I am Apprentice to the common 
law of harm. No rook, no reed, no 
rain, only Overhearing in 
the next room The Surrealist's boot growing 
into The foot-soldier's missing hank 
Of limb on the terrible concrete 
in the city Of Tehran. This is 
my house. This is my house. This is 
my house. This is my house. This is 
the hour when no living Creature can 
lean its forehead into my 
hand. The owl in the barn is so still No 
one takes my word that he is real. 
In the pamphlet, on page three, you will 
find me Clutching the yellow parasol 
